<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,1399,1257,1499]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
In describing 
<taxonomicName authority=", Smith" authorityName="Smith" box="[360,674,1257,1284]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Bignonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undulata">
<emphasis box="[360,584,1257,1283]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Bignonia undulata</emphasis>
, Smith
</taxonomicName>
wrote that the species was discovered by Hardwicke who conveyed living plants to Calcutta, but he did not explicitly state that the description was taken from Hardwicke. The species is not included in Hardwicke’s 
<emphasis box="[863,1100,1329,1355]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Asiatick Researches</emphasis>
paper, but the plant was undoubtedly found by Hardwicke. There is drawing no. 
<quantity box="[849,909,1365,1391]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.382" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="in" value="33.0">33 in</quantity>
the Natural History Museum set and four drawings (Vol. V nos. 57–61) in the British Library. Of these, Vol. V no. 57 comes closest to Smith’s tab. 19, though it appears to be laterally reversed. I here lectotypify 
<taxonomicName box="[993,1212,1437,1463]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Bignonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undulata">
<emphasis box="[993,1212,1437,1463]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Bignonia undulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, now known as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sm.) Seem." authorityName="Seem." baseAuthorityName="Sm." box="[189,576,1473,1499]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Tecomella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undulata">
<emphasis box="[189,420,1473,1499]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Tecomella undulata</emphasis>
(Sm.) Seem.
</taxonomicName>
, to Smith’s plate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
